From: nagalakshmi.nandigama@lsi.com <nagalakshmi.nandigama@lsi.com>
Date: Thu, 1 Dec 2011 07:42:40 +0530
Subject: [SCSI] mpt2sas: When IOs are terminated, update the result to DID_SOFT_ERROR to avoid infinite resets
Git-commit: 3ade1ca7ac16a9c5cf5883d6f04e340562c17148
References: FATE#313896
Patch-Mainline: v3.3

Signed-off-by: Nagalakshmi Nandigama <nagalakshmi.nandigama@lsi.com>
Signed-off-by: James Bottomley <JBottomley@Parallels.com>
Acked-by: Hannes Reinecke <hare@suse.de>
---
 drivers/scsi/mpt2sas/mpt2sas_scsih.c |    2 ++
 1 files changed, 2 insertions(+), 0 deletions(-)

diff --git a/drivers/scsi/mpt2sas/mpt2sas_scsih.c b/drivers/scsi/mpt2sas/mpt2sas_scsih.c
index bc63af4..7319ef9 100644
--- a/drivers/scsi/mpt2sas/mpt2sas_scsih.c
+++ b/drivers/scsi/mpt2sas/mpt2sas_scsih.c
@@ -4489,6 +4489,8 @@ _scsih_io_done(struct MPT2SAS_ADAPTER *ioc, u16 smid, u8 msix_index, u32 reply)
 			scmd->result = DID_TRANSPORT_DISRUPTED << 16;
 			goto out;
 		}
+		scmd->result = DID_SOFT_ERROR << 16;
+		break;
 	case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SCSI_TASK_TERMINATED:
 	case MPI2_IOCSTATUS_SCSI_EXT_TERMINATED:
 		scmd->result = DID_RESET << 16;
-- 
